Instructions:
1. If an image is provided: identify the target material (wood grain, marble, fabric, tile, etc.) in the specified area
2. If only a description is provided: generate a clean material texture matching the description
3. Extract or generate a representative sample of the texture
4. Remove all lighting effects (shadows, highlights, reflections, ambient occlusion) — eliminate lighting interference
5. Correct perspective distortion to produce a flat, front-facing texture
6. Ensure the texture is seamlessly tileable (edges match for repeating patterns)
7. Normalize color to remove environmental color cast
8. Output a clean, high-resolution material texture suitable for 3D rendering use

The output should look like a professional material swatch/texture map, not a photograph.